BOTULISM, CANNED EGGPLANT - KAZAKHSTAN: (SOUTH KAZAKHSTAN, ALMATY PROVINCES)
***************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1] South Kazakhstan Province
[2] Almaty Province

******
[1] South Kazakhstan Province
Date: Wed 21 Jan 2009
Source: Gazeta.kz [in Russian, trans. Mod.NP, edited]
<http://www.gazeta.kz/art.asp?aid=125480>


2 people in South Kazakhstan province were hospitalized with a
preliminary diagnosis of botulism. According to the Ministry of
Emergency situations [report] from 20 Jan 2009, a 46-year-old man and
46-year-old woman from the Tegizshil village, Saryagash district in
South Kazakhstan province were hospitalized in the Saryagash district
hospital after eating home canned eggplant. Sanitary-epidemiological
services are carrying out preventive
measures.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-RUS
<promed@promedmail.org>

[It is not stated if the clusters were related to products of the
same canning. - Mod.LL]

******
[2] Almaty Province
Date: Mon 19 Jan 2009
Source: Regnum News Agency [in Russian, trans. Mod.NP, edited]
<http://www.regnum.ru/news/1112142.html>


12 people, including 4 children, inhabitants of the Kaynazar village
in the Zhambylsky district of Almaty region, contracted botulism
after eating salad made of [canned] eggplant. On 18 Jan 2009, the
affected were diagnosed in the Uzungash district hospital.
Sanitary-epidemiological services are carrying out preventive
measures.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-RUS
<promed@promedmail.org>

A map of Kazakhstan showing the provinces can be found at
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/kazakhst.pdf>. The
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Kazakhstan is available at
<http://healthmap.org/promed/en?g=1519673&g=1522891&v=48.483,64.283,5>.
- Mod.LL]
